A '''haversack''', or '''havresack''' is a [[backpack]].

The word originally referred to a bag which riders provide for horses to carry oats (through the French from [[German language]] ''Hafersack'' and [[Dutch language]] ''haverzak'', an oat-sack, a nose-bag for a [[horse]], ''Hafer'' or ''Haver'' meaning [[oat]]s).  In [[Scotland]] and the north of [[England]], the word 'haver' is still used to mean 'oats,' as in 'haver-meal' or 'haver-bread.'

